# t/research/transcript-restart-safety.test — the TRANSCRIPT harvest is crash-safe
# (decision-013), the last post-finish effect to be reconciled. A finished run's
# session transcript is archived even when capture-transcript never completes inline.
#
# capture-transcript was the last fire-and-forget effect: agent-run-finished emitted
# it as an inline Cmd. A crash between logging that message and the archive write
# lost the transcript forever — replay re-derives the Cmd but SUPPRESSES effects, and
# archive-task's transcript special-case SKIPS re-archiving it at finish, so nothing
# backstopped it. Now that AddArchive is content-addressed and idempotent on
# (task_id, filename), a re-drive re-archives no duplicate, so the transcript is
# reconciled like the rest of the fan-out: agent-run-finished records a PENDING
# transcript job; the harvest-reconcile source drives capture-transcript; the effect
# ends with mark-harvested{transcript}, which clears the job.
#
# This proves the FULL crash window: capture-transcript's AddArchive is faulted so
# the effect errors before emitting mark-harvested, the process crashes with the job
# still owed, and the restart recovers it. `fail content archive` targets AddArchive,
# the durable write UNIQUE to capture-transcript in the fan-out (its ReadTranscript
# is a workspace read) — so the memory and reply harvests are undisturbed.

send allow-sender { address kasi@decode.ee }

# --- Faulted run: capture-transcript's AddArchive fails before mark-harvested. ---
fail content archive

deliver {
    from    kasi@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "reconcile"
    body    "reconcile the transfer"
}
task 1 status is awaiting-agent

agent {
    out reply.txt "Reconciled."
}
task 1 status is awaiting-user

# The reply still sent — the transcript harvest is orthogonal to delivery, and only
# the transcript harvest was faulted.
outbound count is 1

# The transcript did NOT land: no transcript row for the task...
archive count task 1 transcript is 0
# ...and the run sits with a pending TRANSCRIPT job, still owed a capture. This is
# the crash window: the transcript would be lost forever if HarvestPending were not
# logged state.
model tasks harvest_pending matches "*transcript*"

# The process dies and comes back: full-log replay rebuilds the pending transcript
# job (the logged mark-harvested{memory,reply} cleared those; the transcript job's
# never came), then the harvest-reconcile source re-fires — this time AddArchive
# succeeds.
crash
restart

task 1 status is awaiting-user                   # replay rebuilt the model
archive count task 1 transcript is 1             # the transcript was recovered — exactly once
model tasks harvest_pending is ""                # mark-harvested{transcript} cleared it
outbound count is 1                              # no second reply — the reply job stayed cleared

# --- Negative control: no fault → the transcript is archived at once. ---
deliver {
    from    kasi@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "again"
    body    "another transfer"
}
task 2 status is awaiting-agent

agent {
    out reply.txt "Done."
}
task 2 status is awaiting-user

# The transcript harvest completed inline (via the reconcile source, no crash):
# archived once, nothing owed.
archive count task 2 transcript is 1
model tasks harvest_pending is ""
outbound count is 2
